15 TO COMMEMORATE THE SEVENTY-FIFTH
16 ANNIVERSARY OF THE SPORT FISH
17 RESTORATION PROGRAM AS PART OF THE
18 AMERICAN SYSTEM OF CONSERVATION FUNDING.
19
20 WHEREAS, more than a century ago, hunters and anglers were among the
21 first conservationists who realized America’s natural resources were in peril
22 and could not sustain unregulated harvesting and habitat destruction; and
23
24 WHEREAS, sportsmen and sportswomen took it upon themselves to support
25 laws that stopped excessive harvesting of fish and wildlife, established
26 state agencies to protect fish, wildlife, and their habitats, and supported
27 special fishing and hunting license fees to help fund the new agencies’
28 efforts to provide healthy natural resources for future generations; and
29
30 WHEREAS, the House of Representatives then and now recognizes that the
31 primary authority to protect and manage fish within Arkansas's waters resides
32 in the state agencies; and
33
34 WHEREAS, upon realizing that license fees alone were insufficient to
35 restore and sustain healthy fish populations, anglers supported excise taxes
36 on fishing equipment to raise additional funds to support restoration and
